The winning outcome will be the driver listed in first place (P1) in the final confirmed Drivers’ Championship standings after all races of the 2026 season have been completed and any investigations, penalties, appeals, or reviews affecting the championship outcome have been resolved. If two or more drivers are tied on points, the FIA’s official tie-breaking procedures will apply (e.g., number of wins, then second-place finishes, and so on). The driver officially declared champion by the FIA following application of tie-break rules will be the market winner.

If the championship result is modified due to penalties, disqualifications, or appeals before the FIA officially confirms the final standings, the market will resolve according to the revised official result. Changes occurring after official confirmation and market resolution will not alter the outcome.

If the 2026 season is officially canceled, abandoned, or if no official World Drivers’ Champion is declared for 2026, the market will be voided and all positions refunded.

